Mandela in the new Clint Eastwood film, interpreted by Morgan Freeman
The South Africans say that the new Hollywood movie, Invictus: invincible, tells a lot about the country, their fight and their victories, although some critics say that the roles the play American players.
The history of sport, race relations and Nelson Mandela.
The tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in the South African Republic and its first black president, Nelson Mandela, is interpreted in its biography by the American actor winner of an Oscar, Morgan Freeman.
Freeman said that Mandela, 91 years, asked him in the film.
Another important role is played by Matt Damon.
I said to him: " When I read, I will have to have access to you.
The actor and two years, which received the prize for his role in the drama of Eastwood on the world of boxing milion dollar baby, played the role of the leader of the movement for the abolition of slavery, which ended up being a slave, the fictional president of the US, and even God Almighty. But rarely represented someone who is still alive and, for many people, is as important as Mandela.
The former South African statesman spent 27 years in prison for their efforts to end apartheid in the South African Republic.
He was released in 1990 and for four years, became president of the country.
In 1993 he was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize.
- invincible is a Latin word and the title of a poem by William Ernest Henley, published in 1875.
The challenge was to talk as he
The film is a true story on Nelson Mandela, who joined forces with the captain of the South African rugby team, Francois Pienaar, to help unite the country. Mandela, the new president, knows that after apartheid their nation remains racially and economically divided.
Believes that it is able to unite his people through sport, and that is why he decides to join the rugby players, who belong in the measure to outsiders.
The South African team to the World Cup in 1995.
Freeman worked several years for the history of Mandela to cinemas.
He had another goal to play this role in such a way that is as similar as possible to the reality, said Freeman.
Of course, the greatest challenge was to talk as he.
The actor said that if he and the world political forces in the same area, had tried to meet with Mandela, dine with him, be behind the scenes before his speech.
The most important thing was that I wanted to shake hands with Mandela.
I discovered that the apretarle hand, get their energy, it is transmitted and had the feeling of knowing how you feel, he said.
For me it is important to try to become a different person.
Matt Damon plays the role of François Pienaar, the captain of the national rugby team, which dominated by white players.
The actor said he had six months to prepare for a role in the world of rugby.
He was A great surprise to, when finally met for the first time in their home.
I remember having called the door, he opened and the first thing that I said to François Pienaar in my life was: " in the film much higher. "
Despite the obvious differences between the characters of the players and their real models, and under the management of the director Eastwood, Invictus: invincible received positive reviews and it also talks of ambitions for the Oscar.
The film critic of the daily Variety magazine Todd McCarthy summed up his assessment with these words: " It was a very good story, a film very well done. "
In the reviews of films on the website rottentomatoes. com, Invictus received a 76 per cent of positive assessments.
The secret of the splendour on Norway resolved: the Russians did evidence of a missile
On Norway observed a special of unknown origin.
The Ministry of Defence of Russia ended recognizing yesterday that near the borders with Norway was evidence of an intercontinental ballistic missile.
The launch failed again. The missile, " Bulava ", previously designed to be the pride of the Russian army, is becoming the nightmare of the Russian generals and Prime Minister Putin.
Even his repeated presence in the evidence of the missile has had the desired effect on the success of the test flights.
Bulavá, in most cases, was not flying or there was a failure in the air.
In Russian newspapers write of " Bulavá " and " a missile that not fly. "
A missile that not fly, but shone.
During this, the 13th test, there was no problem.
At the end of the flight of new technical problems in the apparatus.
Probably the engine broke in the third stage of the missile.
This time " Bulavá " was launched from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskoy, floating in the White Sea.
This type of missile launched from a boat that is moving and black at the same time.
It is therefore likely that the light mysterious on Norway, caused by an unidentified flying object in reality outside the failed " Bulavá. "
The Norwegians like from the first moment did not hesitate with a Russian missile.
The generals are saying that this time cannot be simply talk of a failure.
The first two stages of the missile and the breakdown occurred in the third.
In the previous cases the engines were immediately in the first stage.
Although none of the launches went completely without mistakes, according to the management of the Ministry of Defence only six of the 13 were unsuccessful.
The success of almost a 50 per cent full of optimism to the generals and therefore continue to claim that " Bulavá " one day fly without problems and that even will take up to ten blocks hipersónicos nuclear, whose total weight of 1.15 tonnes.
