Hyundai fulfilled the requirements of the trade unions. all the extra work
The direction of the car factory in Nošovice agreed with the unions cancel all the extra work.
Precisely because of the frequent extra work, unions said on Monday the emergency by strike.
The information was confirmed by Petr, the spokesman of the factory of automoviles Hyundai.
The direction, however, wants for this year to agree with the unions a Saturday.
We cannot resign ourselves to our plan, it is essential that proposed voluntary extra work for the Saturday, 19 December is to say, it will work in two shifts, said Vaněk.
According to the Sedmička. cz server, the company offered a bonus of 400 CZK employees to work the time on Saturday.
The bonus will be paid for last Saturday, 28 November.
According to Vaňka, the company decided to change the way to motivate their employees with the extra work offered.
Employees can collect the bonus for overtime or can take a free day on 28 December, prolonging a day, Christmas, mentioned Vaněk.
Moreover, all employees of the shifts on Saturday will receive money for travel and for food.
Because the extra work was the most urgent and challenging of the comments and complaints of trade unionists and strikers, who stopped the production last week, the direction yesterday afternoon decided to cancel all the extra work for the month of December, mentioned.
The employees of the cars were forced to work two hours more besides shifts of eight hours and this situation virtually every day until last week.
After signing the agreement the unions cancel the emergence of strike.
Another negotiation between the direction of the factory and trade unionists must be on Monday morning.
The head of the trade unions Petr Kuchař said on Wednesday, that if they commit to meet the requirements and the document was signed, are willing to cancel the emergency by strike.
The situation in the car factory was aggravated last week on Wednesday, when about 400 employees spontaneously entered strike by frequent extra work.
Also protested against the poor conditions of payment and the alleged harassment.
The direction was that employees had to work overtime to meet the requirements and to provide the cars.
Trade unionists in his declaration of emergency by strike on Monday, also demanded that none of the employees, who last Wednesday interrupted the manufacture, were penalised in any way.
As regards the extra work, the trade unions demand that the company is reduced to a minimum.
Moreover, this year required for this work remuneration of 5,000 crowns.
The car factory in Nošovice Hyundai now has 2,000 employees.
The production was launched last November.
Until last September manufactured approximately 80,000 cars; its current production potential is 200,000 cars a year.
A Czech discovery: a substance effective until in encallecidos ' HIV virus
The team of scientists Czechs and Germans evidence of new compounds capable of holding the spread of HIV in the body
The main advantage of this substance improved is the fact that it is also effective against the virus resistant to medicines.
In some cases this is more important than the fact that the compound is not as effective in a common variant of the virus, as some drugs accessible.
The disease AIDS can be cured until now.
However, the lives of patients can significantly thanks to a mixture of drugs that prevent the replication of the HIV virus in the body.
However, their use has many side effects.
If the replication of the virus is not removed completely, will create the so - called resistant virus; against them, no longer work medicines.
The work of the experts of three institutes of the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic, VŠCHT Prague and the University of Heidelberg demonstrates the ability to dominate the resistance of the virus.
Showed that substances called metalocarboranos have effect on the albumin, responsible for the spread of the HIV virus.
The metalocarboranos are composed of boron, hydrogen, carbon and cobalt.
These compounds are blocking the spread of the virus in a different way to all drugs used today, and therefore can solve the problem of resistance.
In its work scientists find new, ' improved ' compounds, prepared knowing the molecular mechanism of its link to the albumin of the virus.
The metalocarboranos have a three - dimensional structure: two cages poliedros composed of atoms of boron, hydrogen and carbon are united by the atom of metal, in this case by cobalt.
A traitor and resilient virus
The proteasis HIV is one of the HIV virus, and it is essential to the life cycle of the virus.
Without the proteasis of HIV, there is the fragmentation of the HIV virus and not create mature and infectious corpúsculos of the virus.
If we stop the proteasis HIV, stop the spread of the virus in the body of the patient, the scientists explained in a press report published by the Institute of Organic Chemistry and biochemistry in the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic.
In an article published in the scientific journal Journal of medicinal chemistry scientists describe a series of compounds, in which two pairs of cages (see the table) are united by a short series organic, which continues to be amended systematically.
A little weaker, but more effective
The evidence of the effect of this series of substances against the proteasis HIV was conducted in tube, and also against their variants, obtained from patients with HIV.
The effect of the metalocarboranos in the common variant of the enzyme is not as strong as in the medicines used, however do not lose their effect in the resistant variants, in which the drugs often do not work.
The mechanism of the single effect, its other qualities such as the biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of other chemical changes to the metalocarboranos are interesting compounds for research with the aim of proposing effective drugs against HIV, said Pavlína Řezáčová, the head of the laboratory of Biology in the Institute of organic chemistry and biochemistry and the Institute of the genetica in the Academía of science.
