Any other person may appear in its place, " said the representative of the public prosecutor, Marie - chrsitine Daubigney.
Finally, the court decided that once made the trial on the admissibility of Mrs Bettencourt - meyers.
Managerial revolution or end of the intelligence of business?
If nothing changes in the management of the big French companies, our fight for the development of the intelligence of business will have been in vain ...
More than ten years ago, the attitude of the direction of large companies with regard to their employees recalls the position of companies with regard to consumers before the revolution of marketing: it is that the partners to join " values " from above as before it was imposing on the consumer products designed for the technical factory.
To put the customer in the heart of the company, the revolution of marketing gave to the strategies of the conquest of markets ... although the authoritarian temptation to impose products that are unrelated to the factors of preference for customers is repeated regularly.
A demobilisation of employees can end in a deadly.
The suicides at France Telecom, PSA and Renault are only the tip of the iceberg of a much more general phenomenon that affects particularly executives.
This demobilization serious commits the intellectual development of all the functions of the company, especially of the R& D and, even more, of the intelligence of business.
Indeed, the (business intelligence) demands that all the parties involved (...) have a proactive behaviour and a forward - looking vision "; it needs a commitment on the part of employees that is completely opposed to the recommendations of an authoritarian direction.
For that reason, we convened a managerial revolution, which would be the partners in the centre of the concerns of the company as the customer.
Opinion polls have a relative utility
Do domestic opinion polls, as the questionnaire by Orange among their employees, will encourage the managerial revolution in practice?
Unfortunately, fear not.
- In principle, because I was able to verify that, faced with a new situation, and after many twists and turns, all companies end up doing essentially ... what always! B989
- secondly, because the authoritarianism, one of the conditions of power, is growing in proportion to the importance of their own failures.
- finally, because the majority of managers have a simplistic view of human behavior.
As from large schools of engineers, interpret the psychology mechanistically.
Take, for convenience, the former behavioral theory that the " American " recently, and that the institutes of studies and the media were largely behind their backs.
In this way, to suggest that it is possible to handle the " commandos " (sic) of the commitment of the executive, a recent research by Ipsos published in Le Figaro. fr reaffirms to the managers in a position of management, unsuited to today's world.
Identifying and measuring the factors of mobilisation
On the contrary, the managerial revolution necessary for the proper functioning of modern companies, is taking a vision of human behavior.
It consists in integrating into all reasoning or practice of business management, a basic fact: for employees, the commitment to the company is only possible if it is clearly as a means to realize their dreams, ambitions and projects.
Today, only the studies from the analysis Motifuncional take this concept of the motivations of employees.
The studies showed that they judge his company based on a predetermined doxa that allows them, through the image of the company, to evaluate what it offers them to achieve their own projects of life.
Thanks to the identification and measurement of the factors of mobilization, managers can monitor, forecast and anticipate its " social performance " and derecursos human " in the place ".
In this way, create a favourable ground for the development of a strong and effective business intelligence.
