Road Transport: three marathon negotiations to ensure the supply of Christmas
After three sessions of negotiations, the health sector unions of roads and the TLF (transport and logistics of France) , the only organisation employers who stayed until the end, arrived on Friday afternoon to an agreement that puts an end to the slogan of strike and the threat that falls on the supply of Christmas.
During the session of signatures on Friday evening, the Secretary of State for transport, Dominique Bussereau, was " delighted " with the agreement, after several negotiating sessions, which began on Wednesday morning.
After a second night of discussions, the negotiators farewell at the dawn of the Friday with the hope of quickly signing the text of the agreement at the end of the morning.
Even when three organisations (Fntr, Unostra, Otre) retired by the door.
But a meeting of more than six hours that began at 11 H was necessary for all agree and the text is firm to 18 h.
The conflict " has been very damaging for business " and " it was feared that disturbs the end of year holidays, " Bussereau said.
The text provides for an increase of 4% for the lowest salaries (in the local and regional road transport) , and 2.9% for the highest (transport) .
The rate per hour rises of 8.72 euros to 9,06 for low wages.
It is not much, but we start with great disadvantage, explained Patrice Clos (FO) .
If so, we are going to give the order to our militants that there are no more cuts or blockages in the centres of supply.
But there can always be some rebellious, added.
Philippe Grillot, President of the TLF, acknowledged that it is " a good agreement ", although it was " difficult to grant increases to higher wages taking into account the international competition ".
According to him, the increases will be in the order of EUR 170 per month for low wages and 100 to 120 euros for the highest.
It is an agreement with common sense and that respects employees, Maxime Dumont (CFDT) , while Thierry Douine (CFTC) is recognized as a " historic agreement ".
For Richard Jaubert (CGT) is " an acceptable compromise. "
The agreement also provides for an increase in the travel expenses of 3% and the holding of general assemblies of road transport in the first half of 2010, which will address the issue of an extraordinary pay and modernisation of the collective agreement.
Bussereau said that " a low of EUR 100 million on employers ' was the subject of an amendment to the government in the finance bill of correction for 2009, the National Assembly voted Thursday night.
The government will ask the Senate to vote " under the same terms.
The signing of TLF allows that the agreement is implemented, firstly, to businesses in this organisation and, secondly, the entire profession, in the event that the Minister of an extension.
It will be " as soon as possible, " assured Bussereau.
The opposition of employers ' organisations could only delay the process.
The Fntr complained that it was a " business of naive ", as the EUR 100 million " had already been promised to the sector to offset part of the CO2 tax.
The Secretary of State for Transport forced us to negotiate in an emergency situation, not as a conclusion to an analysis discussed by the parties, but to frustrate those who want to eat Turkey in the next Christmas Eve dinner, regretted the Unostra.
For the Otre, the agreement puts at risk " the stability of many SMEs in the sector over the next 12 months.
