The Turkish justice dissolving the party, a decision with serious consequences
The Turkish Constitutional Court ruled on Friday in favor of the dissolution of the main party in the country, a decision that immediately provoked demonstrations of anger in the Kurdish community, in the south - east of the country and in Istanbul.
This decision could complicate the task of the government, which has just lend a hand to the Kurdish community trying to put an end to 25 years of conflict.
The Democratic Society Party (DTP) was dissolved because it had become the focus of activities that undermined the independence of the state and its indivisible unity declared to the press by the President of the Court, Hasim Kiliç, after four days of deliberations.
The decision of the 11 judges was unanimous, but a majority of seven votes was needed to get the dissolution, indicated Kiliç, and added that 37 of the leaders of the party, including its President Ahmet Türk and the Member Aysel Tugluk, are removed from political life for five years.
The judge also announced the lifting of the parliamentary immunity of which enjoyed Türk and Tugluk, and the confiscation of the assets of the party by the Treasury.
The DTP has 21 seats in Parliament (550) .
Their leaders warned before the verdict that members of Parliament before being parliamentarians without partisan label.
The decision comes in the wake of a procedure that launched the Supreme Court prosecutor, Abdurrahman Yalçinkaya, in 2007, which accused the DTP of obeying the " principles " of the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) , considered a terrorist organisation by Ankara and by many other countries.
Many observers believe that the DTP is the legal political window of the rebels of the PKK.
However, the party claims it has no " organic links " with the PKK, but refuses to qualify as a terrorist organization and called on the government to negotiate with him.
The verdict of the Court intervenes at the time that the government extends a hand to the Kurdish community a series of measures to strengthen their rights, so that the Kurds stop supporting the PKK and put an end to the conflict.
The leaders of the DTP claimed that a dissolution could lead to an escalation of tensions in the south - east Anatolian, where a large number of demonstrations against the conditions of detention of the leader of the PKK, Abdullah degenerated into clashes with the police over the last few weeks.
Since the announcement of the justice, thousands of demonstrators gathered in front of the premises of the DTP in Diyarbakir, the main city of in south - east populated mostly by Kurds.
The forces of order threw tear - gas grenades and used water cannons, while the demonstrators throwing Molotov bombs or stones with slingshots.
In Istanbul, also focused around 100 people.
After the verdict, said that the decision of justice going to " deepen the despondency ".
Turkey can resolve this issue (Kurdish, NDLR) dissolving a party, told the press.
The government, formed by a party from the Islamist movement, also regrets the decision.
In principle, we are opposed to the closure of parties.
This does not solve anything, said the energy Minister.
This decision boycotted the opening of democratic launched by the government, said the political analyst Ahmet Insel.
We can expect, of course, a reaction of the PKK, added.
This Thursday, the PKK was awarded an attack in which seven soldiers were killed three days earlier in the north of Turkey, one of the most bloody in recent months.
New Silicon Valley
For many years, was seen as a secret city, inaccessible to the Western visitors.
Selenogrado, one of the 10 districts of Moscow, was in the Soviet Union a heavily guarded site for the secret investigation.
Today, the community of 216,000 inhabitants, 37 kilometres from the centre of Moscow, is regarded as the " Silicon Valley ".
Here are important centres of research and production of micro and nanoelectronics.
Since September 2008, representatives of Selenogrado have contacted the seat of scientific Riedberg in Frankfurt, with the university institutes and companies of the innovation Centre of Frankfurt (FIZ) .
There were various mutual visits and now, on Wednesday, Selenogrado and Riedberg signed in Frankfurt a " Protocol of close collaboration. "
The Vice - alcalde Juri Rosljak and the mayor of Selengrado, Anatoly Smirnov, led the Russian delegation; Frankfurt signed the head of planning services.
In the 2010 travel to a seminar in Selenogrado representatives of FIZ and managers of small and medium - sized enterprises of the research centre of natural sciences.
Scientific exchange
It is a scientific exchange.
But it also addresses trade relations.
The companies will have the chance to put a foot in the Russian market.
To change the Russian scientific companies want to have access to contracts in Germany.
Selenogrado is the headquarters of major companies and research institutes.
They include, for example, the Moscow Institute of electronic technology, the large corporations Sitronics and Rossijskaja Elektronika.
The community was founded in 1958 as the so - called " city of socialist " for research.
Selenogrado (literally translated as " green city ") received its name from the landscape of mountains, in which settled research facilities.

The size of Stuttgart 21 places for nothing is sufficiently high.
For supporters of the project is simply as " the new heart of Europe ".
The law on. S21 is much more than the reduction of a railway station, more than a monstrous construction project, which the capital of the region of Banden - württemberga a decade of chaos of construction sites.
Stuttgart 21 emerged from the spirit of the 1980s.
With terminals, which end up in the middle of the city, were at that time fossils of engineering of the 19th century, acting as brakes of a modern rail traffic, formerly an enormous amount of time was needed for locomotives back ahead.
Rolling, stopped in their tracks continue the journey; but it should be done.
And why should disappear terminals: in Frankfurt and Munich.
And in Stuttgart: a step, which is approximately half of the journey of the trans - European lines of operation between Paris and Budapest/Bratislava; hence the slogan of " heart of Europe ".
The S21 really will be initiated, despite the fact that the visions of the 1980s are no longer compatible with reality.
Even the most ambitious designers have known that in the capital hessiana and Bavarian is almost unpayable implement the reduction.
The Rail terminals of course also have more problems of entry and exit, since there are locomotives reversible with unity tractora and cart driver at both ends.
However: Stuttgart 21 including the new tranche built ice towards Ulm already will be initiated.
The Federal politicians and communal have prepared well.
The rail continues, also because the risks of large individual infrastructure projects of the Republic is the taxpayer and not the state.
From the point of view, the project still justified to some extent.
It creates new urban space, many green areas, probably of generated by computer the designer.
For the rail transport system S21 is harmful.
The station and the road are designed for the transport of persons, which was attributed to the huge growth typical of the 1980s.
At that time was not given the competition from low - cost flights.
But the modern transport policy must first deal with strengthening the transport of goods, since the rail transport is considerably more environmentally friendly than those made by lorries on the roads.
However, the new sections in construction are good for freight trains due to the intense gradients.
Even more serious is that the S21 also indirectly affects many other rail projects.
More than six billion euros should be buried in the Zuavos.
That is the official figure.
Experts believe that it is more realistic to between 10 and 15 billion.
It is certain that in the next decade the money in other crossings and narrow passages in the network.
In total 60 bigger projects are in the list of the Ministry of transport.
One of the most important is the expansion of more than 180 kilometers of rails long through the Rhine Valley.
Since 1987 the route at a slow pace.
Be urgent here the accelerator pedal.
However the S21 acts as a brake.
The stretch of the Rhine Valley will be the bottleneck for the international transport of goods: through the heart of Europe.
