The university careers are
Partial success for students: After a year of strikes related to education, the Ministers of Education and culture of the Federated States finally relented. In a meeting of the Ministers of Education and Culture with university rectors, both sides agreed to try to improve conditions in the cases of bachelors and masters.
Students should in future should be able to overcome their careers.
For example, agreed to reduce the burden of examinations: basically each module of the race must end with a single examination.
In addition to examine the workload of students, and it wants to ensure a " real and justifiable ".
The policy and the universities want to simplify the recognition of results of examinations between universities inside and outside Germany.
The federated States commit themselves to draw more flexible rules structural together to careers of bachelor and master.
Regulations of the federal states that diverge from this, should no longer exist.
Less examinations
Since the beginning of the student protests in June the ministers of education and culture and the rectors of universities talk constantly of the improvement of power and conclude with a successful career (estudiabilidad) .
Now for the first time there was talk of a content.
The so - called accreditation Council agreed to drastically reduce the number of tests: " Each module ends with a single review, " says in a document of 30 pages, which seeks to regulate the approval of the academic careers.
With the significant reduction of the burden of examinations " is intended to prevent the development in the wrong direction, which would significantly affect the estudiabilidad, explained the director of the accreditation Council, Mr Reinhold Grimm.
Moreover, in the future, " estudiabilidad " must be the decisive criterion in the configuration.
The modules and content must be examined in detail in terms of unnecessary restrictions of students in the choice of ..
The courses.
The Students would have " the right to obtain more spaces, which enable and encourage the own initiative ".
These rules resort for new careers, but also in the examination of existing careers.
These must be " reacreditar once every five years. But this would mean that it would take until 2015 to examine all races.
Those responsible for this would be nationwide 10 accreditation agencies, which are under the supervision of the accreditation Council, which was installed by the Länder.
The ministers of education and culture called the federated States in October influence on the agencies, in such a way that the amount of raw and examinations are not too strict or demanding.
In some Länder universities and technical schools already agreed with the ministries to adopt such measures.
Until now only Renania - platinada assured provide additional resources for the subsequent development of the Bologna process.
With this money universities must implement mentoring programs and student advice, as well as strengthen and foreign offices.
The land and the universities seek to have EUR 10 million for these purposes.
At the beginning of 2010, the government wants to bring to Parliament a novel of the university law.
As it should be enough just one examination for the completion of a model of career.
The shape of the race should be made more flexible, it also wants to ensure the recognition of assessments in other universities and facilitate the accessibility to master.
Until the end of next year is intended to examine all the careers about their " estudiabilidad ".
This Thursday, the government and the opposition discussed again on the conditions of the land.
Part of the praise there was also criticism about the decisions.
In the board at the federal level of the university groups Juso (Young Socialists) seexigía, that the shape of the education policy is no longer should be " behind closed doors " of the ministers and the university rectors.
At the latest after the strikes of education, now students as main involved should be able to say.
The President of the board of university rectors (HRK) , Margret Wintermantel, gave their support to students: " We need the experience of the students, " said Thursday in a meeting with the Ministers for Education, with which the HRK deliberated on a joint document on reform.
For the Union of education and science (GEW) the Bonn agreements were not quite enough: the union demands a legal right for each student with the title of the possibility of access to a masters degree.
