The federal States have quecontratar significantly more teachers.
But about greater access to the Masters, the Ministers of Education did not comment.
More than a footnote about Herta Müller
" enter and exit from Germany is virtually no control, " says the first line of a poem by Werner Söllner in fragments of language, in which tematiza experiences of arrival in Germany by a dissident, who won their freedom, but lost the environment of their language.
Werner Söllner, who was born in 1951 in Banat, Romania, worked initially as a professor of German and English in Bucharest, and then as reader in a publisher of children's books, before moving to Frankfurt in 1982.
To Söllner gave him several prizes for literature, in 1993 the memorable lessons or talks of poetry in Frankfurt the Goethe University, and since el2002 is director of the forum of literature in Hesse in the Mousonturm in Frankfurt.
Given that speak quite last Tuesday during a meeting in Munich on " German literature in Romania in the mirror and the mirror disfigured their dossiers "
Visibly insecure and ashamed, Söllner read a statement in which he admitted participation as IM in the Romanian secret service against fellow writers alemanes - rumanos, among other Richard Wagner, William Totok, Franz Hodjak, and Helmuth Frauendorfer.
In conjunction with some of those present in 1989, Söllner had received the prize of the German language.
The Attempts of recruitment had started slowly, early in 1971.
" Therefore I am someone who is not sufficiently defended in the face of attempts to provocation of fear of the Securitate ", ended Söllner.
The lyric is IM Walter.
Almost at the same time of the award of the Nobel Prize for literature to Herta Müller and his controversial literary unparalleled with the mechanisms of dictatorial rule, shaking the literary scene and in particular the community of German authors of Romania for a case that highlighted the divisions and the evil of a political system, which is based in control and espionage.
Werner Söllner is what we know so far, is not only author, but also a victim.
In his dossier of Securitate IM Walter had played a role, said the scientist literary Michael Markel after the confession of Söllner, and stressed the positive influence for him delim Walter.
He had apologised or defended in all the difficult points for him, said Markel.
" I feel the need to do this, " he said.
The declaration of Söllner in this way and in the face of this was unexpected, the confession of a ex - disidente and his work with the Romanian secret service, however, is not surprising.
Germany would have been a comfortable refuge for spies of the Securitate - spitzel gewesen, wrote Herta Müller in the month of July in the weekly " Zeit ", having read its own dossier of 914 pages.
Those involved probably will have speculated and known in some cases, what names were hidden behind the pseudonyms of Sorin, and also of Walter.
Unlike the review of the files Stasi with a controlled procedure in Germany, dealing with the issues of control by the Securitate is still quite unclear.
A systematic clarification was boycotted and hampered in recent years.
A National Council for the clarification of the files of the Securitate (CNSAS) , corresponding to the authority, was formed in 1999, and the delivery of the files since then is more.
Since 2005, there is a law that regulates the administration of files.
An interview, following the award of the Nobel Prize for literature to Herta Müller, evidence of the influence of former members of the Securitate in Romania is still quite large. In this interview a head of the Securitate of Temesvar spoke disparagingly of the condecorada.
" She is psychosis, " in the end only once.
The infamy of power seemed to be able to show without turns in the form of freedom of opinion.
Of course, questions inevitably arise with the case Söllner, as so often when there is blame silent.
Why right now? who is caused damage? The calm reaction of the listeners in the face of the confession of Söllner leaves hope that the continuation of this history is governed by the desire for knowledge and not so much by the award of blame and shame.
For the genesis of the work of Herta Müller, who yesterday accepted the Nobel Prize for literature, is more than a mere footnote.
