Ardent mourning in Berne: time and again the challenging Kevin Johnsonn was causing the world champion Vitali Klitschko with words and gestures.
But after 12 hard rounds, the Ukrainian defended his title of heavyweight in the version of the WBC.
The trial of the judges was unanimous.
Hamburg: Vitali Klitschko remains heavyweight world champion.
The champion of 38 years in the version of the association expired on the evening of Friday to Saturday in Berne the American Kevin Johnson by unanimous decision by points (120: 108, 119: 109) .
For Klitschko was his third successful defence of the title since his return in October 2008.
Earlier, the Ukrainian was already twice world champion of the WBO and WBC associations.
Unfortunately, it was not possible to make the noqueo that all had hoped.
Klitschko expanded its balance sheet to 39 triumphs in 41 professional fights, twice had to give due to injuries.
The Johnson had to accept the first defeat in his fight number 24.
