In the air attack in the United States, requested by the German commander, Colonel Klein, according to the report of the investigation of NATO, died or were injured to 142 people.
The Greens, the SPD and the left called on Saturday in the Federal Chancellor Angela Merkel (CDU) to take immediately to the federal parliament and to clarify what Gutenberg really knew about the incident.
Mrs Merkel has to clarify whether a strategy of intentional killing is part of the federal government's policy in Afghanistan, and if the chancellery, the army and the information service have adopted this new strategy, Jürgen Trittin and his colleague from the Greens Renate Künast.
