Cowardly aggression
Last week, my mother of some 70 years of age walking by our neighbourhood in the municipality of Fuenlabrada when a group of young people between 15 and 18 years spent together, and our dog, a copy of race, rescued the perrera and with no more than six kilos of weight and, without a word, two kicks that left the dog Malherido.
Our indignation is because we do not find the fun in a wanton aggression to a small animal and helpless, which incidentally, was tied.
Add to this the embarrassment that resulted in a Mrs strolling calmly and, when lashed to these individuals, came to fear for their physical integrity, as a madman that attacks an animal, is able to do the same with a woman, a child, an old man or, in short, anyone who is weaker than himself.
The incident occurred at 5 p. m. on a Tuesday anyone by a district traditionally calm.
The dog was crying all day.
By the way, we put a complaint in a nearby police station that we doubt that serves much and not to generate sensitivities, just to clarify that the cowardly killers were Spanish.
The outrage has led us to denounce this fact.
We do not understand what is happening among young people to consider fun maltreatment free to a defenceless animal that we love, companionship and friendship.
We do not know where they have been good education and respect for animals and people.
Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the hull
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, with the cooperation of the Spanish Foundation for road safety (Fesvial) , has launched a campaign to promote the use of helmets, mainly among the young motorcyclists, reported today both entities.
This initiative seeks to raise awareness about the importance of using the hull, because it is the only element of protection capable of preventing head injuries or even death in the case of an accident while touring motorcycle.
Michelin indicated that this campaign is part of his commitment to road safety, which " goes beyond design and manufacture products every day more secure " and said that also contributes to this goal through other actions of educational and informative.
This new campaign to promote the use of the hull in the motorcycle, under the slogan ' to be or not to be ', will have a first phase in which will be distributed posters in more than 500 workshops motorcycles, with the goal of maximum dissemination.
To conclude, Michelin stressed that road safety is a constant concern " for the company, as being a manufacturer of tyres for two - wheeled vehicles, one of its main purposes is to develop insurance products.
The sale of light commercial
Almost two years later, the market for light commercial vehicles is beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9.425 units enrolled in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of declines, according to figures from the employers of the manufacturers and sellers Ganvam.
The good thing, not, it should be put on hold because the reference to the comparison - November 2008 - was particularly bad, with a drop of the previous year.
The consequence of this is that, despite the resurgence of the last month, the accumulated in these 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January 95.853 units have been sold together all vehicles that make up the hotchpotch of the light commercial: derived from cars, pick up, pickup trucks, vans and light trucks/chassis.
Also, have not disappeared the clouds that most affect their demand, because although they are also purchased by individuals, most of the purchases are made by small and medium - sized companies, which pay in almost 100% of the cases through external funding.
Of closed So that the restrictions in the tap of bank loans, are other factors such as the increase in the levels of unemployment or the persistence of the poor economic situation.
Against this background and unlike cars, have been of little help aid to the purchase of the 2000e.
To them eligible, in addition to individuals, the self - employed and SMEs to acquire a commercial light of up to 3.5 tonnes with a level of CO2 does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, but the number of operations has been.
Yesterday, since Ganvam returned to recall the need to devote special attention on the part of the administration to these vehicles and also to industrialists (trucks and buses) .
The association of sellers predicts a similar to the year 2010, for which estimated a fall in sales (cars and 4x4s) of 19%.
The emergency brake assist is already mandatory
As happened with the anti - lock brakes ABS and about the stability control of ESP, emergency brake assist systems will have to be a compulsory element in European cars.
In fact, they already are in all passenger cars and light commercial vehicles of new registration, while the rest is set for a period until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to increase the protection of pedestrians although, on his way to work, it can also help prevent many collisions.
The assistant to the emergency brake what it does is increase the pressure on the brakes in the event of an emergency, the system detects the pisotón that gives the driver.
But this does not always maintained that pressure until the end.
According to a study carried out by the manufacturer of components for car Bosch, the third part of the drivers involved in an accident had not come to step on the brakes before the collision and half of them did not use any force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
The intervention of the aid, however, requires the maximum the brake system, reducing the distance that used the car to stop.
According to a study by the EU itself, if all cars were equipped with this type of elements, could be avoided each year up to 1,100 fatal accidents involving pedestrians.
The reduction will be even greater - it is estimated that one of every four claims would be avoided with damage to popularize people - when the so - called intelligent emergency brake system.
In this case, the vehicle is equipped with a system that (through a radar or a house) detects obstacles and alerted the driver, in addition to act slightly on the brakes.
If the driver reacts, helps increase the pressure on the pedal, if necessary.
In the event that it fails to react, and although the collision is inevitable, the device exercises maximum effort to the brakes to minimize the damage.
