After his speech, followed by the President of gas Natural - fenosa, Rafael Villaseca, gave the press a few of what had raised in the subcommittee behind closed doors.
For the President of Iberdrola, Spain needs to invest EUR 50 billion by 2020 and other 60 billion between that date and 2030, provided they are kept open nuclear power plants in operation today.
Otherwise, the necessary investments will not be of 60 billion, but up to 95 million.
That Iberdrola believes that in the next decade investments should not be used to increase the capacity in a generation, but in distribution networks and interconnections international
From 2020, the issue is changing and will have to increase the power.
Its bid focuses on both gas and coal plants with carbon dioxide capture and, above all, of renewable energies.
In this case, believes that we need new 18,000 MW, with other sources of support "
Galán, who believes that the draft law on sustainable economy that the government has just approved is in line with what his company has been calling for, did not want to make blood with the Royal decree to encourage consumption of coal, which contradicts the national policies to combat climate change.
In his opinion, there is " a clear commitment to long - term " in this sense, despite the " sporadic ", as the president of Iberdrola.
Be that as it may, Galán believes that investment decisions, although they are in the long term, it must begin to take longer because late maturing and a stable framework is needed to address them.
