The timetable set by the administration sets the award for the summer of 2010 and the start of construction in December next year.
In spite of the fact that this step of payment would be open to traffic in recent months in 2014, it is not anticipated that the work is finished until 2016.
The tunnel began to be designed in 2005.
Include two lanes by sense, electronic toll system and a complex ventilation system.
The Queensland government will provide 500 million Australian dollars (308 million euros) to its financing.
