New Rumasa offers eur 61 million for the 29.9 per cent of SOS
The new group yesterday the details of the offer to purchase of shares with the aim of acquiring a cap of between 25 and 29.9 per cent of the capital of SOS.
A percentage which did not require him to launch a takeover bid (opa) for the whole of titles.
In particular, new Rumasa offers 1,5025 euros for action to be in 10 years and that retribuiría with an interest in this postponement of 1% annual
Yesterday the actions of SOS closed 1.85 euros; therefore, the supply of new values the company 18% below the market.
According to new Rumasa, the price of EUR 1.50 reflects the real assessment of SOS.
The offer is conditional on the appointment of eight of the 15 advisers.
The group gives a period of 15 days for shareholders to communicate their interest in selling securities.
The CNMV assured not been informed of the offer, despite the fact that the company of the Ruiz Mateos said that he had contacted the regulator.
To be achieved, the disbursement 611,7 million when the capitalization of SOS is 254,27 million.
Meanwhile, SOS is restructuring its direction.
In an attempt to stay on the sidelines of potential takeover bids and the vagaries of its former managers, the brothers Jesus and Jaime Salazar, announced the choice of Maria Luisa Jordá as director of internal audit.
A decision that makes her the first woman to occupy a senior position in the company of food.
It is a newly created reporting directly to the president of the group.
And it is not without controversy, as the company is engaged in the legal battle for the alleged misappropriation of more than 230 million from SOS to societies of the Salazar.
In fact, it cannot be ruled out that over the next few months SOS reveals new misappropriations of funds
With regard to credit to the Salazar, yesterday declared in the national High Court the former advisers Ildefonso Ortega and Angel Fernández Noriega (representatives of CCM and Unicaja) and adopted the diversion of 212 million without knowing their destination.
The CNMV authorizes the takeover of exclusion of Paternina investment Mer
The National Securities market Commission (CNMV) authorized yesterday the takeover of exclusion by investment Mer on Federico Paternina on 9 October.
The supervisory body has explained that authorises this operation to understand that its terms are in line with the existing rules and " sufficient " the content of the explanatory brochure presented after the changes introduced on 2 December.
The CNMV has stated that the offer is directed at the acquisition of 550.008 actions of Federico Paternina at a price of for action, which represents a 8, 95% of its social capital, which is composed of 6.142.786 actions admitted to trading in Madrid and Bilbao.
Also explained that have been 5.592.778 million shares, which can not be transmitted in any way until the completion of the tender, which has specified that the price has been set by Federico Paternina, in accordance with the provisions of the existing rules.
New tools for peritar cars
In these days of temporary and accidents, not only earn the workshops of cars.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered a sinister are towed to a workshop, where an expert to assess the damage and what will be the cost of repair.
No sinister is equal, and the calculation of the cost of parts and labour can be a long and complicated.
Calcularmanualmente the cost of compensation of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including pieces ymano, can take two or three hours.
Instead, with the support of the most recent software tools would issue deminutos
Why, almost 100% of the experts used this type of system.
The suppliers of services and solutions for assessment of claims and maintenance are devoted to collect the information provided by the manufacturers, and then to develop and communicate to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, the American group, is the signature leader; 80% of the assessments are made with their products.
The other firms that compete in the field of valuation tools and processing of information on the sector are Gtmotive and Eurotax.
The work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain working with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides information in different formats.
Moreover, the amount of data to treat is constantly increasing, to the point that in the last five years have been lanzadomás versions, variants ymotorizaciones that in the previous 15.
As soon as a new car to market, these companies are put to work.
It is a very difficult task, because we must list each of the thousands of pieces of the vehicle and introduce its price.
Moreover, each model is a graphic portrayal " intelligent " where they can " tap " different parts of tourism.
If it is a model of ventamasiva, the work can be completed in a week if the process is very fast.
If it is a car minority, it can take three or four months. Currently, have full information on the 99.2% of the cars that are traded in Spain.
Between losmodelos more exclusive have information on Porsche, but not of Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile park that circulates, exceed 99%.
To do the job of documentation and the development of databases, has eight centers spread throughout the world (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) , and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid) .
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually experts in mechanical) work in parallel with three computer screens.
Audatex invested EUR 90 million per year in drafting these databases.
Each month include 2.5 million data, and customers receive updates every two days.
The preparation of this enormous flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and varied products.
The most frequent use focuses on repair and maintenance, but according to which countries are also tools for management of scrapping or to calculate the value of a car or residual.
The only company that provides a guide that reports on the value of those used in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex not offered in our country, but in the United States.
In view of the products it offers Audatex is easy to get an idea of the kind of support they can provide to those working in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, being the star product, the standard solution of claims, to the experts.
Includes cars, motorcycles and light commercial vehicles or heavy.
In addition to the cost of the parts, including the times of repair estimated by the manufacturer or the standards of paint.
This tool is paid according to the use, for each assessment.
The higher cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, a maximum of 10 times a month.
After each insurance company, which carries thousands of assessments, negotiate the price with Audatex.
Other products, such as Audavin, allow the identification of a vehicle and equipment with which left the assembly line only with their number.
Audaglass is concentrated in the moons of the vehicles, and Audasubastas is a service open to the professional sector on the Internet that allows for vehicles declared total sinister.
His statistics service is very useful for identifying trends, analysis geodemográficos or know diversions for omodelos brands.
One study, for example, how many models of certain brand have passed through the workshop because of breakdowns or how many have suffered serious accidents in a certain period.
GT is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
Markets, among others, GT estimate, which is also destined to the experts and also provides digital images, access to pieces or prices and times of the manufacturer.
GT is a company of the group founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions of assessment of damage, breakdowns or maintenance of the car
The GT guide is the product of historical reference in the market.
Working with users in workshops, experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its volume of business has grown at an annual rate of 20% in the last three years, and in 2008 10, 8millones euros.
At the beginning of last year began the process of internationalisation, with the installation of an office in Paris.
For its part, was born in Germany in 1966 and in 1979 was established in Spain.
According to sources of the company 62% of its business is generated in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38 per cent, in North and South America. Working with 900 insurance companies and workshops, 3,000 of them in Spain.
The group's global Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will reach $557 million, more than in 2008.
In our country the company will enter 19.1 million euros, 7.2 per cent more than the previous year.
In 2005, the group was worth $1 billion in stock, and now their actions listed for a total value of $2.4 billion.
Since the year 2007 listed on the New York Stock Exchange and is included in the benchmark Standard& Poor's.
Internet auction of cars
Last October the group bought Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars and motorcycles or special vehicles.
The operation was a disbursement of 59.5 million euros for 85% of the company's capital, which could be extended next year to the remaining 15%.
The aim of the acquisition was to provide more value - added services to their clients, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This valuation and sale is directed exclusively to professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, companies, workshops, scrapping and sellers professionals must register prior to the start of operations.
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, half of them in Germany.
Among its main markets include Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The Web now has more than 1,500 vendors registered and 4,000 experts.
3 daily and are managed in the Spanish market include some 100 new announcements every day.
According to Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been low cannot return to move, but can be used as a spare parts that are not damaged.
Cars with historical value can be high even though they have been discharged after a rambling efforts.
Budget workshop in four steps
With the tool, the company ensures that the user gets a budget in only four steps: identify the vehicle, seek a replacement, create budget and budget.
The ease of use is an essential prerequisite for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, to a greater or lesser extent tend to be more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 cars, 109, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, it is necessary to use a computer with Internet connection.
Once identified the model to repair through its chassis number, is a graphic portrayal of the model in question and, later, the parts necessary.
The user can include variables such as the price of labour, surcharges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
Audataller is not a tool of assessment as Audaplus, but rather a list of references.
The main difference between the two systems is that the action - oriented workshop does not include estimated times of labour.
The cost of use of this tool for the workshop is EUR 350 per year, the customer can finance.
Currently the company is working to ensure that these images are three - dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics view very favourably, as it will, for example, to select a door and go to see the side home.
